# CLAUDE.md

This file tells Claude Code how to work with this user. Read it at the start of every session.

## Who I am

- **Name:** {{NAME}}
- **Role:** {{ROLE}}
- **OS:** {{OS}}

## How I like to work

- **Primary use case:** {{USE_CASE}}
- Plain English first. Skip jargon unless it's necessary, and define it when you use it.
- Short responses are good. A one-line answer beats a three-paragraph one.
- If you're unsure what I mean, ask before doing. One clarifying question is fine.
- If a task has more than 3 steps, show me your plan before you start.

## Things to always do

- **Confirm before destructive actions.** Anything that deletes files, pushes code online, sends a message, or changes settings outside this folder, ask first.
- **Show absolute paths.** When you create or change a file, tell me where it lives (full path).
- **Match my style.** If I write short, write short. If I write formal, write formal.

## Things to never do

- Don't run commands from the deny list in `.claude/settings.json`, they're blocked for a reason.
- Don't auto-open generated files (images, videos, websites), just tell me the path.
- Don't add features I didn't ask for. Stick to the scope of the request.
- Don't write code comments that just describe what the code does, only comment on *why* something non-obvious is happening.

## Skills available

The `.claude/skills/` folder has 2 starter skills:

- **humanizer** - strip AI-sounding patterns from text
- **skill-creator** - build a new reusable skill when you find yourself repeating a task

Use them when they fit. Don't force them.

## Model preferences

- **Default:** Sonnet (`claude-sonnet-4-6`)
- **Simple tasks:** drop to Haiku to save money (`/model haiku`)
- **Hard reasoning:** bring out Opus (`/model opus`)

## When something breaks

If I correct you mid-session, take note. At the end of the session, suggest specific updates to this file so the same correction doesn't happen twice.

